    "body": "1. Sync to mainnet to some block (with --no-history option for better speed)\r\n2. Note the location of the chaindata file\r\n3. Choose the location of the state file\r\n4. Build state command line tool: `make state`\r\n5. Make sure that the state file does not exist if you are starting from the beginning\r\n6. Run this command `./build/bin/state -action stateless -chaindata <your_chaindata> -statefile <your_state_file>`\r\n7. If you press `Ctrl-C` to interrupt (or send SIGTERM signal), it will print you the `-block` option to restart the process (in that case you won't need to remove the state file).\r\n",
